Defining the scope.

100
00:08:48,887 --> 00:08:50,008
The project scope, yeah.

101
00:08:50,028 --> 00:08:55,690
The facility needs, issues, the scope is crucial because that basically becomes your specification for what you're going to build.

102
00:08:57,311 --> 00:09:01,033
It's something that needs to be done up front before you start getting into

103
00:09:01,913 --> 00:09:06,197
You know, the design, you know, what windows, what colors, all that stuff, that's down the road.

104
00:09:06,237 --> 00:09:09,621
But you need to first define what you're going to include in the new facilities.

105
00:09:10,101 --> 00:09:14,906
And the needs need to be real, not nice to have wishes.

106
00:09:15,727 --> 00:09:22,794
You've got to put what the real needs are, and those need to be driven by educational needs that you can then begin to measure success on that.

107
00:09:25,217 --> 00:09:35,061
And the building committee in doing this work, I refer to it as a cost reduction mentality.

108
00:09:37,202 --> 00:09:47,185
Don't start with just expanding, expanding, expanding when in fact that drives costs through the roof that now you're going to have trouble getting support from the community.

109
00:09:47,645 --> 00:09:50,847
If we want this to go forward successfully, it has to be

110
00:09:52,012 --> 00:09:57,338
compatible with what the public is willing to pay for such a new facility as this.

111
00:09:58,219 --> 00:10:06,568
One of the interesting things was, and I think this project scoping, what the needs are, needs to be done, it needs to be done sooner rather than later.

112
00:10:07,890 --> 00:10:13,076
I was in a meeting, one of the building committee meetings, and one of the members of the committee

113
