So that's why you've got a year in advance of that.

121
00:11:03,826 --> 00:11:06,047
We need to start focusing on the scope.

122
00:11:06,767 --> 00:11:10,890
and the true requirements, the needs, which drive the square footage right now.

123
00:11:11,190 --> 00:11:12,351
Now, do that first.

124
00:11:12,411 --> 00:11:13,612
Yeah, get it out of the way.

125
00:11:15,693 --> 00:11:17,174
So that's all important stuff.

126
00:11:17,314 --> 00:11:21,957
Now, the thing that I think, I mean, this concerns everybody.

127
00:11:22,738 --> 00:11:30,824
I mean, really, I mean, can you give us, I guess, like, the word is like viable, financial,

128
00:11:32,113 --> 00:11:35,396
solutions, funding options, I don't know what you would call it.

129
00:11:35,496 --> 00:11:43,802
Well, you know, once you've got the scope identified, it starts, you start getting a sense of how, what the facility might cost and so on.

130
00:11:44,002 --> 00:11:49,287
What you've really got to make sure is that, well, make sure, maybe that's not the right way to phrase it.

131
00:11:49,327 --> 00:11:56,052
You've got to do whatever you can to have the cost in line with what the needs are.

132
00:11:57,965 --> 00:12:01,047
Because ultimately that drives the tax implications to the public.

133
00:12:01,407 --> 00:12:01,687
Yes.

134
00:12:01,787 --> 00:12:02,948
In a major way.

135
00:12:03,048 --> 00:12:10,071
And I think, you know, I am of the opinion that the sooner you get that cost information, even if it's preliminary.

136
00:12:10,351 --> 00:12:10,611
Right.

137
00:12:10,771 --> 00:12:16,534
To give people a range of what this could be potentially costing, that's going to get them engaged.

138
00:12:16,874 --> 00:12:18,995
That's going to have them come to the table to say,

139
00:12:20,095 --> 00:12:22,038
Why should it be in that range?

140
00:12:22,318 --> 00:12:23,620
What could you do to reduce it?

141
00:12:23,900 --> 00:12:25,823
We would like to see this versus that.

142
00:12:26,304 --> 00:12:28,266
It's going to create this dialogue.

143
00:12:28,446 --> 00:12:28,687
Right.

144
00:12:28,827 --> 00:12:32,292
And this seems to be perhaps for

145
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:56,186
reasons they don't want to stop putting the cost out now because they're afraid it's going to scare people uh... you know i think you know to see what your program is about we've got to have information to make informed decisions so even though it might create some some heartburn in the community initially it will create a dialogue which then can help

146
00:12:57,366 --> 00:13:14,628
the building committee understand what the community wants and is willing to pay for so very very important I think um so I mean being financially accountable to the people that live here is huge that's you know

