00:14:16,621 --> 00:14:20,586
Can you tell us, what should citizens know?

157
00:14:21,910 --> 00:14:23,752
about the MSBA process.

158
00:14:23,792 --> 00:14:36,264
And I just want everyone to know, the MSBA is the Massachusetts School Building Authority for those, you know, sometimes we throw initials out and people have no idea.

159
00:14:36,344 --> 00:14:40,268
So it's the Massachusetts School Building Authority.

160
00:14:43,020 --> 00:14:46,803
You know, I'd like to hit on, like, how do we maximize the funding from them?

161
00:14:46,823 --> 00:14:47,543
Yeah, we'll talk about that.

162
00:14:47,563 --> 00:14:48,404
That would be nice.

163
00:14:48,624 --> 00:14:54,248
But basically, you know, the value that the MSBA provides to any community engaging in such a process.

164
00:14:54,829 --> 00:14:56,049
They've been doing this for a while.

165
00:14:57,270 --> 00:14:59,312
They know they have a whole process.

166
00:14:59,472 --> 00:15:00,393
They have steps.

167
00:15:01,594 --> 00:15:14,285
They lead communities through how to do that, what they need to deliver, when they need to deliver it, how they need to work with the professional organizations they ultimately hire, like the architects, the owner, project managers, and so on.

168
00:15:14,846 --> 00:15:18,349
And that's, you know, for most communities, we don't do this that often.

169
00:15:19,129 --> 00:15:23,954
So it's a new game for most people, even with the building committee with experience.

170
00:15:25,495 --> 00:15:27,756
people who have skills.

171
00:15:28,636 --> 00:15:32,718
You're getting into an area that is not common or familiar ground.

172
00:15:33,138 --> 00:15:39,920
The MSBA leads you through all that, gives you all the timetables, sets the dates, meets with you.

173
00:15:39,940 --> 00:15:47,343
They'll come out and do assessments of your existing facilities, which I think they've obviously, by this time, they've done that to the high school.

174
00:15:47,683 --> 00:15:52,325
They'll provide guidance on some of the professional service firms that you need to engage with.

175
00:15:53,105 --> 00:16:05,513
And so it's a very helpful process, and you can go on their website, and there's more than enough information if you're so inclined to find out more of those details.

176
00:16:07,154 --> 00:16:13,939
But also what it helps, and one of the things that they require, the state requires, is community input.

177
00:16:14,739 --> 00:16:24,344
Now, as I often say, most people, it's not about input telling you as you get into the building discussion, oh, I want this color or that wall.

178
00:16:24,724 --> 00:16:25,564
It's not about that.

179
00:16:25,864 --> 00:16:32,848
It's more about people's sincere inputs on what they would like to see in their facility.

180
00:16:32,908 --> 00:16:39,151
So for example, the traditional high school and the vocational school, just use that as one example.

181
00:16:39,871 --> 00:16:41,152
What do people feel about that?

182
00:16:41,772 --> 00:16:43,233
They've been traditionally separate.

183
00:16:44,233 --> 00:16:48,517
But now there's some talk about integrating to a degree those two programs.

184
00:16:49,078 --> 00:16:50,779
What do you, the community, think about that?

185
00:16:51,159 --> 00:17:09,777
Because as you get inputs from the community on that, it refines or gives direction to the building committee in the school administration which way to go, which has an impact on space, numbers of classrooms, where to locate the facilities or the rooms inside the building.

186
00:17:10,457 --> 00:17:15,139
That's the kind of input that comes about with good active engagement from the community.

187
00:17:15,519 --> 00:17:15,759
Yeah.

188
00:17:15,899 --> 00:17:21,082
So, the MSBA really does have a big role.

189
00:17:21,302 --> 00:17:21,402
Oh.

190
00:17:21,482 --> 00:17:22,322
They really do.

191
00:17:22,402 --> 00:17:30,326
I mean... You have to meet the deadlines, meet the requirements, the reports, drawings.

192
00:17:30,506 --> 00:17:35,668
All of that has to be met in order to, if you want to get any funding, you have to meet those requirements.

193
00:17:36,048 --> 00:17:36,429
Okay.

194
00:17:37,109 --> 00:17:38,610
So, that's a big part of it.

