00:17:54,248 --> 00:17:57,570
What is it that drives the project costs?

197
00:17:58,271 --> 00:17:59,812
What's the main thing behind that?

198
00:17:59,912 --> 00:18:02,873
Well, the funding eligibility?

199
00:18:02,893 --> 00:18:04,715
Yeah, driving the costs, yeah.

200
00:18:04,735 --> 00:18:15,161
Well, I've got something that can explain some of those a few, but on the funding itself, which again is provided by the MSBA if you've met all the requirements.

201
00:18:15,381 --> 00:18:16,182
Right, okay.

202
00:18:16,902 --> 00:18:22,145
What happens, and I think you can see it on the screen there, all communities are started and baselined at 31%.

203
00:18:23,848 --> 00:18:29,029
Based on a number of different things, criteria you meet, you could get additional percentage points.

204
00:18:29,249 --> 00:18:32,210
You might get two points for this, one point for that.

205
00:18:32,450 --> 00:18:42,452
There's things about maintenance, energy conservation, the socioeconomic profile of the community.

206
00:18:42,812 --> 00:18:45,593
There are a number of things that will get you additional percentage points.

207
00:18:45,593 --> 00:18:46,313
points, which is good.

208
00:18:46,813 --> 00:18:49,914
So you might go from $31,000 to $35,000 to $37,000.

209
00:18:50,474 --> 00:18:55,856
And again, that is a percentage of funding the state will provide against the total cost.

210
00:18:55,896 --> 00:19:04,238
Now, something to really be clear on, they will only provide funding for eligible project costs.

211
00:19:05,158 --> 00:19:06,880
